      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Mesh convergence study must demonstrate <5% change in all three QoIs between the penultimate and final mesh refinement levels.",
      "rationale": "A four-level mesh refinement study was conducted (element edge lengths 1.5 mm, 1.0 mm, 0.6 mm, 0.4 mm). QoI changes between the 0.6 mm and 0.4 mm meshes were 1.8% (stiffness), 2.3% (yield force), and 1.1% (force at 40 mm). The 0.6 mm mesh was selected as the production mesh. Discretization error is within acceptance bounds."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
